reviewText:
Very funny stuff, and it is all my kind of humour.

I'll buy all the series one day ; on the cover it says that the episodes are in colour ; not so, but that should not deter anyone from buying these shows and getting a better laugh here than from anything this side of a Mel Blanc/Jerry Lewis Picture.

In case you were wondering, this collection has five episodes from each of the four seasons. Only one (the pilot) should overlap with the Season 1, Volume 1 disc, so you can purchase both and get a pretty good sampling of the series at a good price.
The seasons are too expensive so you get a lot for a little money with this
It is very entertaining to watch these old shows. Good quality picture and funny content. I would definitely buy again. Thanks.
I bought this DVD for my husband's birthday.  This series is not available on any of our channels, so he really appreciated the surprise!

I remember the series as a kid and it was funny then  but as an adult it seems way funnier now than when I was younger.  Its just  clean kind of slap stick humor from an era when such was readily available vs. now.  Great value for the money ......
wish there were more to pick from, i liked it very much.  i would buy more if there were to choice from.

I never missed this show when I was a teenager.  Loved all the characters.  I am enjoying watching this show again.  Wished all the other episodes in the series. were on DVD now.  Nice to see clean shows again.
Silly plots and tiresome buffoonery which years ago might have been popular but terribly tiresome today.  Three 20 Timeless Episodes in trash.
Love it. It's one of my favorite shows. thanks.

A really great collection of classic episodes from 1 of the finest comedies with a great comedic cast,Ernest Borgnine and Tim Conway,among others. I was born in 1990 but remember the show and watched it with my dad,I saw this and got it thinking we would dig a trip backwards
First off,the pictures in black and white, although the disc and art and even intro are in color,the show remains b&w.barely any cigarette burn style glitches or years inrolls of film.great show,volumes low,so turn it up loud and surround effects didn't make a difference as an option on the DVD. However 2 discs 20 episodes.gives ya the season # & episode # in the shed order. Excellent show.my dad digs it & I dig it,very funny classic show.
